avid-larbi

For the second episode of Substack on Film: London, we spent the day with D=
avid Larbi , a poet, author, and podcaster known for his improvised rhymes =
and steady optimism.
Most people know David through the short, polished poems he posts online=E2=
=80=94bursts of joy delivered from the street, the park, wherever he happen=
s to be. We wanted to showcase what sits behind that energy: the quiet thou=
ghtfulness that fuels it.
We planned to meet in the park, but the weather had other ideas. Instead, w=
e wandered through a local library, talking softly about writing and routin=
e while waiting for the rain to clear. When the sun finally came out, David=
 stepped outside and, without hesitation, started to rhyme=E2=80=94an off-t=
he-cuff poem inspired by nothing more than the wind in the trees.
You can read more of David=E2=80=99s work on his Substack [ https://substac=
k.com/redirect/13b465c9-b907-4e98-a8b8-f80760810c33?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMW5qZ29rIn0=
=2EAgI-vvm-koCoupjCwZXCGwdYu_D1iw9ec=
HmePkbA3ys ]. We=E2=80=99ll be back next=20=
week with another episode of Substack on Film: London.

